This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it focuses on improving the efficiency of exploration for deep Q-learning agents in dialogue systems. Additionally, the paper mentions techniques such as Thompson sampling and Bayes-by-backprop neural networks, which are commonly used in natural language processing and dialogue systems. 

The paper also touches on topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and reinforcement learning (cs.SD, cs.NE), which are all relevant to the development of efficient exploration techniques for deep Q-learning agents. However, given the focus on dialogue systems and natural language processing, cs.CL is the most likely sub-category.
